    • Method Detail

      • getSynchedPackets

        List<Registration> getSynchedPackets()
        Gets the list of Registration data with the following statues:
        1. SYNCED
        2. EXPORTED
        3. RESEND
        4. E
        Returns:
        the list of Registration entries with the above statuses

      • pushPacket

        ResponseDTO pushPacket(File packet)
                throws URISyntaxException,
                       RegBaseCheckedException
        Push the Registration packet to the server using Packet Receiver service. The packet has to be syched before pushing to server.

        Returns the ResponseDTO object.

        If the packet had been pushed successfully, SuccessResponseDTO will be set in ResponseDTO object

        If any exception occurs, ErrorResponseDTO will be set in ResponseDTO object

        Parameters:
        packet - the packet to be pushed to server
        Returns:
        the status of the packet push
        Throws:
        URISyntaxException - the URI syntax exception
        RegBaseCheckedException - the reg base checked exception

      • updateStatus

        Boolean updateStatus(List<PacketStatusDTO> packetUploadStatus)
        Updates the client status of the uploaded packet to PUSHED in Registration table
        Parameters:
        packetUploadStatus - the list of packets which are uploaded
        Returns:
        true if status of all uploaded packets are updated

      • uploadPacket

        void uploadPacket(String rid)
        Uploads the required registration packet to the server after creation of registration packet.

        The registration packet will be sync with the server and then packet will be uploaded

        The client and server statuses will be updated after packet is uploaded

        The above process will be done only when EOD process is turned OFF

        Parameters:
        rid - the registration id of the Registration Packet to be uploaded to the server

      • uploadEODPackets

        void uploadEODPackets(List<String> regIds)
        Uploads the registration packets after approval/rejection during EOD process when EOD process is turned ON

        The registration packet will be sync with the server and then packet will be uploaded

        The client and server statuses will be updated after packet is uploaded

        The above process will be done only when EOD process is turned ON

        Parameters:
        regIds - the RIDs' of the registration packets to be uploaded to the server

      • uploadAllSyncedPackets

        void uploadAllSyncedPackets()
        Uploads all the registration packets which are already sync with the server during Machine Re-Mapping process

        The client and server statuses will be updated after packet is uploaded
